  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You command your hive to swarm around your enemy and attempt to encapsulate them in a mold of honey.</p><p>Select one create you can see within range. That creature must make a Dexterity saving throw as honey is sprayed at them by countless bees. On a failed save, the target becomes <strong>Slowed</strong> for the next minute. A creature <strong>Slowed</strong> this way counts as being within difficult terrain.</p><p>A creature slowed by this jutsu can as a Action on their turn make a Strength (Athletics) check vs your Ninjutsu Save DC to end this jutsu's effects on them.</p><p><strong>At Higher Ranks</strong>: For each range you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost of the jutsu by 3 and targets by +1. Alternatively, you can choose to target the same creature twice. If you do, the creature only makes their saving throw once and on a failed saving throw, the target is also <strong>Restrained</strong> until the start of their next turn.</p>",
